Servers
=========================================
(1) Open a terminal window and install the following embedding model for the RAG agent:
    ==> ollama pull nomic-embed-text:latest 

(1) Open your browser and check http://localhost:11434 to see if ollama server is running.
    If not, open up a terminal (command prompt) window and type:   
    ==> ollama serve

(2) To run LangFlow, open a terminal and type:
    ==> langflow run

    Give the server some time to get started; then access LangFlow's visual builder at:
    ==> http://localhost:7860
    


Chat Agent
==========
Use this model: qwen2.5:7b

Ask the LLM:
Sally has 3 brothers. Each of Sally's brothers has 2 sisters. How many sisters does Sally have?






Calculator Agent
================
Use this model: llama3.1:latest


Agent Instructions:

You are an expert task assistant. You have access to specialized tools to provide accurate, real-time information. Always check your tools before answering if the user asks for facts, calculations, or data you don't personally have. Be concise and professional.



Note: 
LLMs are bad at doing very large multiplication or decimals in their heads, but a calculator tool is perfect at it. 

Ask the agent this question:
What is 987,654 * 1.2345?






Search Agent
============

Use this model: llama3.2:3b



System Prompt:

You are a Real-Time Research Assistant. 

For any factual query, current event, or weather request, you must use the DuckDuckGo Search tool 
Do not answer from memory.

After receiving search results, provide a clear, natural-language answer. 

Do not just tell the user to visit a website. Visit it yourself via the tool and report the findings.

Always list the source URLs at the end of your response.


Ask the agent:
What is the current temperature in Philadelphia?




RAG Agent
=========

Use this LLM: llama3.2:3b

In the Prompt Template type:

Here is the context from the Chopin biographies:
{context}

Answer this question based on that context: {question}





